\begin_layout Standard
Neural circuits transform activity and produce activity that is either sent
 to higher brain areas or to muscles to elicit behavior.
 A very simplistic example of this idea is that of the reflex arc, where
 sensory information is relayed to motor neurons in the spinal chord, in
